 to taste (see tip)"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"3 medium eggs"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"½ tsp bicarbonate of soda"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"200 g cherries in syrup, pitted"},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Icing"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"80 g dark chocolate, 70% cocoa, small pieces or callets"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"60 g butter, diced"}],"nutrition":["per 1 slice","1546 kJ \/ 369 kcal","4.9 g","51.8 g","16 g"],"hintsAndTricks":["Gingerbread spice can be made in your Thermomix: In a clean and dry mixing bowl, place 4 cinnamon sticks, 2 tsp ground ginger, 5 g nutmeg, 10 allspice berries, 10 g cloves, 25 cardamom seeds (shelled), 1 star anise, and 20 black peppercorns then grind <b>1 min 30 sec\/speed 10<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula. If necessary, grind again <b>30 sec<b>\/speed 10<b>. Store in a sealed container.<br>"],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","1h 25m","10 slices"]}